Description: Fragment of foot of Attic black glaze pottery cup-skyphos; convex outer edge, and fillet at junction of bowl and foot; glazed black on exterior and inner face of foot; reserved: outer face of foot, resting surface and underside of floor; inscription cut on inner face of foot.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 496)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1526)
